Introduction

This plot contains data collected from a weather station in McCall, Idaho. This data goes back to March, 1906. The data includes daily minimum and maximum temperatures at the station location on the given date.

When you click the Knit button a document will be generated that includes both content as well as the output of any embedded R code chunks within the document. You can embed an R code chunk like this:

strDates <- as.character(climate_data$DATE)

Ploting Data

See guide #3 that I updated to make this stage better explainedâ€¦hopefully!

plot(TMAX~NewDate, climate_data, ty='l') # This works!

TMAX.lm = lm(TMAX ~ NewDate, data= climate_data)
slopeintercept = coef(TMAX.lm)

plot(TMAX ~ NewDate, data= climate_data, las=1)
abline(slopeintercept, col="red", lwd=3)

       (TMAX.lm.sum = summary(lm(TMAX ~ NewDate, data=climate_data)))
